                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470920-name-582" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-582" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-582" type="surname" value="TAYLOR"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-582" type="given" value="JOHN WILLIAM"></interp>JOHN WILLIAM TAYLOR</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Thames-policeman.</hi>) On the 1st of Sept. I went on board the lug-boat "Desire," in the London Docks, and found the pri<lb></lb>soner stooping in the hold by a cask of brandy—I smelt brandy, and saw some spilt on the floor—this gimlet was by the cask—it was wet, and smell of brandy—I found this bottle, took it up, and said, "Holloa, old fellow, what have you been up to?"—he said, "Forgive me this time, it is brandy; I got it out of this cask"—I took him to my inspector.</p>
